      {
        "wrappers": [
          "info-div"
        ],
        "template": "<p>A hazardous waste is one that presents one or more of the following dangerous characteristics: explosive, carcinogenic, oxidizing, corrosive, flammable, infectious, irritating, toxic, harmful, mutagenic and/or ecotoxic. If a waste does not have any of the above characteristics, it will not be considered hazardous waste and, therefore, its management will be carried out together with the rest of urban waste.<br><br>Among the hazardous waste produced in the teaching and research laboratories of the University, chemical waste, group III or bio-medical waste, radioactive waste and waste from experimental animals stand out. <strong>(SANDACH)</strong>.<br><br>The management of the University's hazardous waste is carried out through the Radiological protection and Waste Section of the ACTI with an external management company.</p>"
